    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last Updated: July 15, 2026</p>
<br>
    <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
    <p>
      Kumral Design<br />
      Senefelderstraße 3, 65205 Wiesbaden, Germany<br />
      Email: <a href="mailto:mail@deniz.studio">mail@deniz.studio</a><br />
      Website: <a href="https://deniz.studio">https://deniz.studio</a>
    </p>
<br>
    <h2>2. Data Processing</h2>
    <p>
      We limit the processing of personal data to what is necessary to operate
      this website and to respond to inquiries you send us. We do not use
      cookies, social media plugins, or any tracking that requires your consent
      under the GDPR or the German TDDDG (formerly TTDSG). The processing that
      does take place is described below.
    </p>
   <h3>2.1 Hosting with GitHub Pages</h3>
    <p>
      This website is hosted via GitHub Pages, a service provided by GitHub, Inc.
      88 Colin P. Kelly Jr. Street, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA ("GitHub").
      When you access this website, GitHub processes technical data, including
      your IP address, to deliver the website content. This processing is
      technically necessary for the functionality and security of the website.
    </p>
    <p>
      We do not have access to these technical data or any server logs from
      GitHub Pages that would allow us to identify individual visitors. The legal
      basis for this processing by GitHub is our legitimate interest in providing
      a functional and secure website (Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR). You can find
      GitHub's Privacy Statement here:
      <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement"
        >https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h3>2.2 Website Analytics (Databuddy)</h3>
    <p>
      To understand how this website is used and to improve it, we use Databuddy,
      a privacy-focused, cookieless analytics service. Databuddy does not set
      cookies, does not use device fingerprinting, and does not collect data
      that can be used to identify you personally or to track you across other
      websites. For this reason, no consent banner is required.
    </p>
    <p>
      The service processes anonymized, aggregated information such as pages
      viewed, referring website, approximate region (derived on the fly from a
      truncated IP address that is not stored), device and browser type,
      interactions (e.g. clicks, scroll depth), performance metrics, and errors.
      The legal basis for this processing is our legitimate interest in
      operating and improving a functional website (Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR).
      You can learn more about Databuddy here:
      <a href="https://www.databuddy.cc/privacy"
        >https://www.databuddy.cc/privacy</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h3>2.3 Contact Form</h3>
    <p>
      If you use the contact form on this website to reach out to us, we process
      the information you provide: your name, email address, and the details of
      your inquiry (such as your company or project name, a description of what
      you do, the type of work you are looking for, your budget range, and any
      additional message). We use this information solely to respond to your
      request and to explore a possible collaboration.
    </p>
    <p>
      The legal basis for this processing is Art. 6 para. 1 lit. b GDPR (steps
      taken at your request prior to entering into a contract) and, where
      applicable, our legitimate interest in responding to inquiries (Art. 6
      para. 1 lit. f GDPR). Form submissions are transmitted and delivered to us
      by Web3Forms, a form-processing service provided by Backpackfy Ventures LLP
      that forwards submissions to us by email. Web3Forms processes the submitted
      data on our behalf as a data processor. You can find Web3Forms' Privacy
      Policy here:
      <a href="https://web3forms.com/privacy">https://web3forms.com/privacy</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      We retain inquiries for as long as necessary to process your request and to
      handle any resulting business relationship, after which the data is deleted
      unless we are legally required to retain it.
    </p>
<br>

    <h2>3. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Under the GDPR, you have rights regarding your personal data, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Right of access (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to object (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise your rights, please contact us at
      <a href="mailto:mail@deniz.studio">mail@deniz.studio</a>.
    </p>
<br>

    <h2>4. Changes to this Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy to reflect changes in our services or legal
      requirements. The current version applies to your visit.
    </p>
